President Donald J. Trump has named Lt. General Joseph Keith Kellogg, Jr. (Ret) as Acting National Security Advisor following the resignation of Lt. General Michael Flynn (Ret). General Kellogg is a decorated veteran of the United States Army, having served from 1967 to 2003. He served as the Commander of the 82nd Airborne Division and was Director of the Command, Control, Communications, and Computers Directorate under the Joint Chiefs of Staff. Lt. General Flynn resigned due to providing incomplete information about his phone calls with the Russian Ambassador. He apologized to the President and Vice President and tendered his resignation. He expressed gratitude for serving the nation and President Trump, and expressed confidence in the leadership of the President and Vice President.